<MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Liveness and OCR Application</MudText>
<MudPaper Class="pa-4">
    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Liveness Detection:</strong> Uses the user's webcam to verify if the person is live.</li>
        <li><strong>OCR:</strong> Allows users to upload identity documents and extracts text from them.</li>
        <li><strong>Tab Navigation:</strong> Provides a clean interface with tab navigation using MudBlazor.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>.NET 6 SDK or later</li>
        <li>A modern web browser</li>
        <li>A webcam (for liveness detection)</li>
        <li>MudBlazor library</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Getting Started</h3>
    <h4>Installation</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Clone the repository:
            <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-username/liveness-and-ocr.git
cd liveness-and-ocr</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Restore the dependencies:
            <pre><code>dotnet restore</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Build the project:
            <pre><code>dotnet build</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Run the application:
            <pre><code>dotnet run</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Open your browser and navigate to <a href="https://localhost:5001">https://localhost:5001</a>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Project Structure</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Pages</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>Home.razor</code>: Main page with tab navigation.</li>
                <li><code>Info.razor</code>: Home tab content.</li>
                <li><code>OCR.razor</code>: Component for reading identity documents and performing OCR.</li>
                <li><code>Liveness.razor</code>: Component for liveness detection using the webcam.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>wwwroot</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>camera.js</code>: JavaScript file for accessing the webcam.</li>
                <li><code>ocr.js</code>: JavaScript file for performing OCR using Tesseract.js.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
</MudPaper>